headline: CF Industries forms JV with JERA, Mitsui for $4 billion low-carbon ammonia plant
summary: Former President Joe Biden passed the largest climate change legislation in U.S. history in 2022, meant to kick off a boom in American clean energy development including low-carbon emission products.  Ammonia producer CF Industries said it is expected to qualify for 45Q tax credit on sequestration of about 2.3 million metric tons of carbon dioxide (CO2) per year.
